      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but can u dig into the \"originalist\" argument a bit more? like, if someone says the court is being \"faithful to the text,\" what's the actual logic they're using to back that up? and then on the flip side, when people call it \"activism,\" what do they actually mean by that? i'm trying to see if there's a real flaw in the originalist logic or if it's just a different way of reading things.",
